fields.name: Istanbul
fields.description: Istanbul served as an imperial capital for almost 16 centuries, during the Roman, Byzantine and Ottoman empires.

fields.name: Berlin
fields.description: Berlin is a world city of culture, politics, media and science.

fields.name: San Fransisco
fields.description: A popular tourist destination, San Francisco is known for its cool summers, fog, steep rolling hills, eclectic mix of architecture, and landmarks.

fields.name: Athens
fields.description: Athens dominates the Attica region and is one of the world's oldest cities, with its recorded history spanning over 3,400 years.

fields.name: Toronto
fields.description: Toronto is an international centre of business, finance, arts, and culture. Its large population of immigrants from around the globe has also made Toronto one of the most multicultural and cosmopolitan cities in the world.

fields.name: Venice
fields.description: A UNESCO World Heritage Site, Venice was a major financial and maritime power during the Middle Ages and Renaissance, and a staging area for the Crusades and the Battle of Lepanto, as well as an important center of commerceâ€”especially silk, grain, and spice, and of art from the 13th century to the end of the 17th.
